lead_paragraph: Astronauts aboard the International Space Station pumped air into an inflatable compartment that could be a forerunner to habitats on Mars and the moon.

headline.print_headline: On 2nd Try, NASA Adds New Space to Station
headline.main: On Its Second Try, NASA Adds Space to Station

snippet: Astronauts aboard the International Space Station pumped air into an inflatable compartment that could be a forerunner to habitats on Mars and the moon.
abstract: NASA successfully inflates pup-up compartment for astronauts at International Space Station, after three day process that took longer than predicted; crew will wait week before entering to ensure safety of pod, which officials see role for in future missions and civilian space travel.
